s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Paul G.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5023:"<p></p><p><a href="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/wordpress-logo-grey-xlarge.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-4184" alt="WordPress" src="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/wordpress-logo-grey-xlarge.png" width="250" height="250" /></a>Last week we told you we were working on an interface to control automatic WordPress background updates directly from within iControlWP.</p>
<p>Today that new feature has arrived and it&#8217;s easy to get started.</p>
<p><span id="more-4393"></span></p>
<h2>How to get started with automatic WordPress Background updates</h2>
<p>We&#8217;ve made it super-easy to kick off automatic updates.</p>
<p>You can enable automatic updates on a per-site basis, or apply it across all your sites and below we&#8217;ll show you how.</p>
<p>Please note: WordPress version 3.7.0 is the minimum required version for this feature.  We will never automatically upgrade a site to 3.7 to meet this requirement.</p>
<h3>Enabling automatic updates per-site:</h3>
<p>As we mentioned before, we&#8217;re using <a title="WordPress Simple Firewall Plugin" href="http://www.icontrolwp.com/our-wordpress-plugins/wordpress-simple-firewall-plugin/" target="_blank">our WordPress security plugin</a>, the WordPress Simple Firewall, as the foundation for our automatic updates.</p>
<p>When you enable automatic updates for a WordPress site within iControlWP, it will do a few things to make sure the site is ready:</p>
<ol>
<li>Ensure your iControlWP plugin is at the latest version</li>
<li>Install (and activate) the WordPress Simple Firewall plugin</li>
<li>Turn on automatic WordPress updates on the WordPress Simple Firewall plugin</li>
</ol>
<div id="attachment_4395" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/icontrolwp-enable-automatic-wordpress-updates.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4395" alt="iControlWP - Enable Automatic WordPress Updates" src="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/icontrolwp-enable-automatic-wordpress-updates-300x188.png" width="300" height="188" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Turn On Automatic WordPress Updates</p></div>
<h3>Enabling automatic updates on all sites:</h3>
<p>Our bulk actions tool serves to perform the same action across all your sites at once. If you have many sites, this can take a while to complete, so it always runs in the background.</p>
<p>To do this, load the Bulk Actions tool (See image below) :</p>
<div id="attachment_4397" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/icontrolwp-enable-automatic-wordpress-updates-in-bulk.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4397" alt="iControlWP - Enable Automatic WordPress Updates in Bulk" src="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/icontrolwp-enable-automatic-wordpress-updates-in-bulk-300x153.png" width="300" height="153" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Enable Automatic Updates in Bulk</p></div>
<h2>Selecting WordPress plugins to automatically update</h2>
<p>Once automatic updates have been enabled on your site, simply then need to select the plugins you wish to have WordPress automatically update.</p>
<p>To do this, each plugin entry on your site listing will have an automatic update slider and you just click the slider to enable the feature.</p>
<p>See image below:</p>
<div id="attachment_4385" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/icontrolwp-site-plugin-manager.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4385" alt="iControlWP Site Plugin Manager" src="http://www.icontrolwp.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/icontrolwp-site-plugin-manager-300x161.png" width="300" height="161" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">iControlWP Site Plugin Manager</p></div>
<p>The simple slider system makes it obvious which plugins are set to automatically update and which aren&#8217;t.</p>
<h2>Suggestions on improvements</h2>
<p>Automatic WordPress updates are a great step forward in streamlining the WordPress management workflow, but it&#8217;s not a one-size-fits-all solution.</p>
<p>You must take care on which plugins and themes you enable this feature and make sure you have <a title="Reliable WordPress backups" href="http://www.worpdrive.com" target="_blank">reliable WordPress backups on-hand</a> to help out if things go wrong.</p>
<p>If you have any suggestions and ideas on how we can improve this tool for you, please let us know.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re not yet signed up to iControlWP and <a title="iControlWP – not just another multiple WordPress manager" href="http://www.icontrolwp.com/2013/05/were-not-just-another-multiple-wordpress-manager/" target="_blank">you don&#8217;t know why we&#8217;re different</a>, grab the 30 day unlimited free trial below.</p>
